      <subsection name="Archive Status Query">
        <p>This interface retrieves the latest archive status of a given product.
        </p>
		<source>
https://&lt;base_url&gt;/&lt;return_type&gt;/archivestatus/[logical_identifier/version_id/true]
          </source>
        <p>When the optional parameters, <i>logical_identifier</i>, <i>version_id</i> and <i>true</i>, are not specified, the query returns the list of archive status of all products. When all three parameters are specified, the query returns the <b>latest</b> archive status of the specified product.
        </p>
      </subsection>
      
      <subsection name="Archive Status List Query">
        <p>This interface retrieves the archive status progression of a given product.
        </p>
		<source>
https://&lt;base_url&gt;/&lt;return_type&gt;/archivestatus/[logical_identifier/version_id/false]
          </source>
        <p>When the optional parameters, <i>logical_identifier</i>, <i>version_id</i> and <i>false</i>, are not specified, the query returns the list of archive status of all products. When all three parameters are specified, the query returns the archive status progression of the specified product.
        </p>
      </subsection>
      
